WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.001 --> 00:00:02.919
Previously on AMC's
"Better Call Saul"...

2
00:00:02.930 --> 00:00:05.223
You. as the lawyer who brought
this case to the firm...

3
00:00:05.234 --> 00:00:07.859
- we can guarantee you 20%.
- That will work.

4
00:00:07.870 --> 00:00:09.380
My brother is sick!

5
00:00:09.391 --> 00:00:10.857
Unfortunately. we have an
issue we need to discuss.

6
00:00:10.859 --> 00:00:12.459
It concerns your malpractice insurance.

7
00:00:12.461 --> 00:00:14.417
I looked at the numbers.
and I can carry us.

8
00:00:14.428 --> 00:00:16.846
I'll take care of my half.
You take care of yours.

9
00:00:16.857 --> 00:00:18.881
Mr. Gatwood? Hi. Kim Wexler.

10
00:00:18.897 --> 00:00:20.230
I've got no choice.

11
00:00:20.232 --> 00:00:22.301
Hector wants to use my dad's business.

12
00:00:22.312 --> 00:00:24.278
I've got cash I can't spend.

13
00:00:24.289 --> 00:00:27.204
You opened this place to
solve a similar problem.

14
00:00:27.206 --> 00:00:28.898
Perhaps there is a way.

15
00:00:45.553 --> 00:00:47.607
_

16
00:01:08.108 --> 00:01:11.000
Mrs. Landry. you're
looking lovely as ever.

17
00:01:11.011 --> 00:01:12.961
Jimmy McGill!

18
00:01:12.972 --> 00:01:14.937
W-What are you doing here?

19
00:01:14.948 --> 00:01:16.898
Oh. I was in the area. and I thought...

20
00:01:16.909 --> 00:01:19.776
I wonder how my favorite
former client is doing?

21
00:01:19.787 --> 00:01:21.284
And I have cookies.

22
00:01:21.308 --> 00:01:22.841
Oh. you're so sweet.

23
00:01:22.843 --> 00:01:24.275
Come on in!

24
00:01:24.277 --> 00:01:25.386
After I made these.

25
00:01:25.397 --> 00:01:28.012
I looked down. and I thought. "Wow!

26
00:01:28.014 --> 00:01:30.335
That looks just like your Felix."

27
00:01:31.412 --> 00:01:33.202
They do!

28
00:01:33.213 --> 00:01:35.323
You're so thoughtful.

29
00:01:35.334 --> 00:01:37.055
I was afraid you wouldn't be here.

30
00:01:37.057 --> 00:01:38.229
Thought. with that settlement money.

31
00:01:38.240 --> 00:01:40.992
you might've moved somewhere swankier.

32
00:01:40.994 --> 00:01:43.921
- What do you mean?
- The settlement.

33
00:01:43.932 --> 00:01:45.898
The Sandpiper case?

34
00:01:45.909 --> 00:01:47.465
Now. that's gotta be
wrapped up by now. right?

35
00:01:47.467 --> 00:01:51.741
Oh. that? That... that...
that... that's still years away.

36
00:01:51.752 --> 00:01:52.804
You haven't settled yet?

37
00:01:52.806 --> 00:01:55.473
No. I don't know all the
details yet. but Erin...

38
00:01:55.475 --> 00:01:59.310
uh. Erin Brill of Davis
& Main... do you know her?

39
00:01:59.321 --> 00:02:04.073
Lovely girl. She reminds
me of a young Mary Martin.

40
00:02:04.084 --> 00:02:06.593
Oh. yes. I-I have met her.

41
00:02:06.604 --> 00:02:09.479
It's a... She's a
wonderful young lady. Uh...

42
00:02:09.490 --> 00:02:11.053
Well. she takes care of all of that.

43
00:02:11.064 --> 00:02:14.159
and she said there's
still a long way to go.

44
00:02:14.161 --> 00:02:16.858
But you've... received an offer. right?

45
00:02:16.869 --> 00:02:19.699
Something sent to you in writing?

46
00:02:19.710 --> 00:02:22.600
I mean. something more than
just Erin and you chatting?

47
00:02:22.602 --> 00:02:23.952
Oh.

48
00:02:27.303 --> 00:02:30.402
It's probably all here in this box.

49
00:02:30.413 --> 00:02:32.911
I can't make heads or tails of it.

50
00:02:32.913 --> 00:02:35.496
but you are welcome to look.

51
00:02:35.507 --> 00:02:36.906
You sure?

52
00:02:36.917 --> 00:02:39.347
Of course. It's you.

53
00:02:40.972 --> 00:02:44.477
Well. uh. I gotta say...

54
00:02:44.488 --> 00:02:48.126
I can't blame you for getting
mixed up with all this.

55
00:02:49.613 --> 00:02:51.245
I mean. these legal notices...

56
00:02:51.256 --> 00:02:54.432
I mean. no one really understands them.

57
00:02:54.434 --> 00:02:57.268
You know. I've got a law degree.

58
00:02:57.270 --> 00:02:59.604
And sometimes I can't even. uh...

59
00:03:03.382 --> 00:03:05.405
I can't even. uh...

60
00:03:11.210 --> 00:03:13.084
You haven't. uh...

61
00:03:13.663 --> 00:03:15.320
accepted this?

62
00:03:15.322 --> 00:03:17.593
Erin says we should wait.

63
00:03:18.522 --> 00:03:19.757
But...

64
00:03:21.765 --> 00:03:24.147
Erin doesn't really matter. does she?

65
00:03:24.158 --> 00:03:27.241
I mean. you're the Class Representative.

66
00:03:27.734 --> 00:03:29.167
That's a big deal.

67
00:03:29.169 --> 00:03:32.103
That means you and you alone decide.

68
00:03:32.105 --> 00:03:34.733
You're... you are the legal stand-in

69
00:03:34.744 --> 00:03:37.075
for your friends and neighbors.

70
00:03:37.077 --> 00:03:39.294
I-I don't know about all that. Jimmy.

71
00:03:39.305 --> 00:03:42.595
I-I just leave it all
to the professionals.

72
00:03:42.606 --> 00:03:44.392
Yeah. sure. sure.

73
00:03:44.403 --> 00:03:46.348
Lawyers know best. but...

74
00:03:47.036 --> 00:03:48.987
I'm sorry.

75
00:03:48.989 --> 00:03:50.321
If you won the lottery.

76
00:03:50.323 --> 00:03:52.190
I mean. you'd take the lump sum. right?

77
00:03:52.192 --> 00:03:54.859
I mean. money now is
better than money later.

78
00:03:54.861 --> 00:03:57.519
- Bird in the hand!
- I suppose.

79
00:03:57.530 --> 00:03:59.597
The more time to enjoy it!

80
00:04:01.034 --> 00:04:03.268
You really should talk to Erin.

81
00:04:03.270 --> 00:04:05.503
She knows all the ins and outs.

82
00:04:05.505 --> 00:04:07.171
Ins and outs.

83
00:04:07.173 --> 00:04:10.286
Yeah. Erin sure knows those.

84
00:04:10.297 --> 00:04:14.080
I'll be happy to talk to Erin. uh...

85
00:04:14.091 --> 00:04:15.980
Just... I just can't help but wonder

86
00:04:15.982 --> 00:04:19.794
if she's taking every aspect into a...

87
00:04:20.222 --> 00:04:21.837
Oh. Jimmy.

88
00:04:21.848 --> 00:04:23.892
I completely forgot...

89
00:04:23.903 --> 00:04:26.324
I'm on my way to chair yoga.

90
00:04:26.326 --> 00:04:27.659
I'm so sorry.

91
00:04:27.661 --> 00:04:29.027
No. it's okay.

92
00:04:29.029 --> 00:04:31.829
Um. I probably should be going.

93
00:04:31.831 --> 00:04:34.205
I have a lot to do.

94
00:04:38.137 --> 00:04:39.330
Hi.

95
00:04:39.341 --> 00:04:40.392
- Jimmy!
- Jimmy!

96
00:04:40.403 --> 00:04:43.322
- Jimmy!
- Rose. Myrtle. Helen.

97
00:04:43.707 --> 00:04:46.238
That chair yoga really works. huh?

98
00:04:46.254 --> 00:04:47.419
You all look 10 years younger.

99
00:04:47.430 --> 00:04:48.512
Oh!

100
00:04:48.523 --> 00:04:50.315
- You honeydripper.
- Hey. hurry up.

101
00:04:50.317 --> 00:04:51.549
It starts in five minutes.

102
00:04:51.551 --> 00:04:52.637
Do you want to come with us?

103
00:04:52.648 --> 00:04:54.519
You're welcome to. We can have guests.

104
00:04:54.521 --> 00:04:57.989
I would love to. uh. but
I'm not dressed for it.

105
00:04:57.991 --> 00:05:00.493
So I'll take a rain check.

106
00:05:00.504 --> 00:05:01.610
Certainly.

107
00:05:01.621 --> 00:05:02.972
Thanks for the cookies. Jimmy.

108
00:05:02.983 --> 00:05:04.996
- Bye. Jimmy! Good to see ya.
- Bye!

109
00:05:09.669 --> 00:05:11.169
That can't be right.

110
00:05:11.171 --> 00:05:13.037
Can't be right.

111
00:05:17.251 --> 00:05:20.509
17.4 total.

112
00:05:21.134 --> 00:05:22.970
33% is the common fund.

113
00:05:22.981 --> 00:05:26.205
So. on 1/15.

114
00:05:26.216 --> 00:05:28.689
15 into 17...

115
00:05:29.955 --> 00:05:31.814
carry the 2.

116
00:05:32.462 --> 00:05:35.197
One million. one hundred and sixty...

117
00:05:36.783 --> 00:05:41.939
One million. one hundred
and sixty thousand!

118
00:05:43.489 --> 00:05:45.169
Holy shit!

119
00:05:50.048 --> 00:05:55.361
<font color="#007700">Synced and corrected by Aaronnmb</font>
www.addic7ed.com

120
00:06:18.382 --> 00:06:20.115
- Mr. Ehrmantraut?
- Yeah.

121
00:06:20.116 --> 00:06:21.274
Sorry to keep you waiting.

122
00:06:21.285 --> 00:06:23.548
It'll be right this way.

123
00:06:23.900 --> 00:06:26.554
Can I get you anything to
drink? Tea. water. espresso?

124
00:06:26.556 --> 00:06:28.564
No. I'm fine. Thank you.

125
00:06:44.914 --> 00:06:46.207
Ms. Rodarte-Quayle?

126
00:06:46.209 --> 00:06:48.211
- I have your next...
- Yes. thank you.

127
00:06:48.222 --> 00:06:50.437
Mr. Ehrmantraut. Lydia Rodarte-Quayle.

128
00:06:50.448 --> 00:06:53.187
- Mike.
- Thanks. Justin.

129
00:06:53.198 --> 00:06:57.039
Have a seat. um... Mike.

130
00:06:57.547 --> 00:06:59.304
HR sent up your start paperwork.

131
00:06:59.315 --> 00:07:02.016
I-9. W-2. Pretty standard.

132
00:07:04.227 --> 00:07:07.729
Could I have your driver's
license and Social Security card?

133
00:07:07.731 --> 00:07:08.882
Why?

134
00:07:08.893 --> 00:07:10.944
My assistant needs to make a copy.

135
00:07:11.929 --> 00:07:15.894
How does this "hire" work.
exactly? Walk me through it.

136
00:07:15.905 --> 00:07:17.839
You'll receive a paycheck from Madrigal

137
00:07:17.841 --> 00:07:19.841
in the amount of $10.000 per week.

138
00:07:19.843 --> 00:07:21.194
I believe at that rate.

139
00:07:21.205 --> 00:07:24.491
your "employment" should be
paid out in about 20 weeks.

140
00:07:24.502 --> 00:07:28.246
Mr. Fring has arranged to
cover FICA. Social Security...

141
00:07:28.257 --> 00:07:30.404
the entirety of the tax burden.

142
00:07:30.415 --> 00:07:32.716
I assume that's all right with you?

143
00:07:35.038 --> 00:07:36.491
Good. So. to that end.

144
00:07:36.493 --> 00:07:39.070
I have you down as a
"logistics consultant."

145
00:07:39.081 --> 00:07:40.816
What is that?

146
00:07:40.827 --> 00:07:44.347
It's a person who consults on logistics.

147
00:07:44.358 --> 00:07:45.952
Does it matter?

148
00:07:46.788 --> 00:07:49.671
I'm not long on logistics.

149
00:07:49.673 --> 00:07:51.546
"Security consultant" would be better.

150
00:07:51.557 --> 00:07:53.632
I used to be a cop.

151
00:07:53.643 --> 00:07:55.877
That will look better
on your "work history"

152
00:07:55.879 --> 00:07:58.273
than your current employer. SMQ Parking.

153
00:07:58.284 --> 00:08:01.109
So. you take my money.

154
00:08:01.120 --> 00:08:03.676
you run it through this
joint. and it comes out clean.

155
00:08:03.687 --> 00:08:05.320
- That it?
- Yes.

156
00:08:05.960 --> 00:08:07.960
Who knows this operation?

157
00:08:07.971 --> 00:08:10.116
You... anyone else?

158
00:08:10.127 --> 00:08:12.382
- No.
- You sure?

159
00:08:13.476 --> 00:08:17.365
May I ask. what precisely
is your concern here?

160
00:08:17.367 --> 00:08:19.148
I am concerned about what happens

161
00:08:19.159 --> 00:08:22.337
if you put my real name in your books.

162
00:08:22.804 --> 00:08:25.490
Your Madrigal is a German company.

163
00:08:25.501 --> 00:08:29.036
One thing I know about Germans
is they love a good audit.

164
00:08:30.804 --> 00:08:34.320
I oversee eight freight terminals
across Texas and the Southwest.

165
00:08:34.331 --> 00:08:37.270
Operating costs range between $800.000

166
00:08:37.281 --> 00:08:39.845
and a million dollars per week.

167
00:08:39.856 --> 00:08:43.535
All due respect. Mike. but your money?

168
00:08:43.546 --> 00:08:45.246
It's a rounding error.

169
00:08:45.257 --> 00:08:47.738
If the IRS or anyone else looks.

170
00:08:47.749 --> 00:08:49.695
you're a contractor for a
multinational corporation

171
00:08:49.706 --> 00:08:53.129
with 114.000 employees worldwide.

172
00:08:53.140 --> 00:08:55.570
You're like every other
person in this building.

173
00:08:55.572 --> 00:08:57.296
Like you?

174
00:08:58.741 --> 00:09:00.945
You think I'm not on the books?

175
00:09:00.956 --> 00:09:03.777
I am. Under my own name.

176
00:09:03.788 --> 00:09:06.748
- This the way you handled it before?
- Handled what?

177
00:09:06.750 --> 00:09:09.884
The money. For Fring's other guys.

178
00:09:10.729 --> 00:09:12.396
Other guys?

179
00:09:13.343 --> 00:09:15.860
This is the first time I've done this...

180
00:09:15.871 --> 00:09:17.171
for anyone.

181
00:09:18.507 --> 00:09:21.113
I don't know what you do. but...

182
00:09:21.124 --> 00:09:24.132
Mr. Fring must think
you're quite good at it.

183
00:09:39.773 --> 00:09:41.449
20 weeks?

184
00:09:41.451 --> 00:09:43.384
The sooner you're off
my books. the better.

185
00:09:43.386 --> 00:09:44.968
Justin?

186
00:09:52.615 --> 00:09:55.209
Can you make a copy of
these. please? Thank you.

187
00:10:00.480 --> 00:10:01.927
What?

188
00:10:04.101 --> 00:10:06.506
This is a very nice office.

189
00:10:06.977 --> 00:10:08.451
Thank you.

190
00:10:11.615 --> 00:10:14.957
Seem to be risking a
lot for a drug dealer.

191
00:10:14.968 --> 00:10:16.581
"Drug dealer"?

192
00:10:20.624 --> 00:10:23.358
If that's all you think he is...

193
00:10:24.125 --> 00:10:26.698
then you don't know Gustavo Fring.

194
00:10:45.971 --> 00:10:48.182
Let me understand you...

195
00:10:48.184 --> 00:10:50.273
you're proposing to double our premiums

196
00:10:50.284 --> 00:10:53.521
on every one of our
practicing attorneys?

197
00:10:54.164 --> 00:10:55.790
We know this is abrupt...

198
00:10:55.792 --> 00:10:58.026
new issues have come to light.

199
00:10:58.028 --> 00:10:59.903
"New issues"?

200
00:10:59.914 --> 00:11:02.285
You mean Mr. McGill's
testimony at the Bar?

201
00:11:02.296 --> 00:11:03.831
That's a part of it. yes.

202
00:11:03.833 --> 00:11:06.121
After 25 years of paying full premiums.

203
00:11:06.132 --> 00:11:08.184
I can count on one hand
the number of our claims.

204
00:11:08.195 --> 00:11:10.199
This is an underwriting
decision... that's all.

205
00:11:10.210 --> 00:11:11.806
You shouldn't take it personally.

206
00:11:11.808 --> 00:11:13.508
In some special circumstances.

207
00:11:13.510 --> 00:11:15.310
we have been known to extend a rider.

208
00:11:15.312 --> 00:11:16.544
What kind of rider?

209
00:11:16.546 --> 00:11:18.413
A senior. management-level partner

210
00:11:18.415 --> 00:11:20.415
who would supervise Charles' work.

211
00:11:20.417 --> 00:11:23.030
attend court and client
meetings with him.

212
00:11:23.041 --> 00:11:24.341
review filings.

213
00:11:24.352 --> 00:11:25.485
The few times we've done this.

214
00:11:25.496 --> 00:11:27.141
it's been for clients
with a high probability

215
00:11:27.152 --> 00:11:29.407
of catastrophic health
failure as a precaution.

216
00:11:29.418 --> 00:11:32.001
What you're saying is that
for any case Charles takes on.

217
00:11:32.012 --> 00:11:34.196
another partner would
be tied up. as well.

218
00:11:34.207 --> 00:11:35.607
and we don't bill a penny more?

219
00:11:35.618 --> 00:11:37.389
This is ludicrous.

220
00:11:37.400 --> 00:11:40.029
The insurance industry
is heavily regulated.

221
00:11:40.040 --> 00:11:41.587
I can think of a dozen infractions

222
00:11:41.598 --> 00:11:43.930
- right here off the top of my head.
- Mr. McGill...

223
00:11:43.939 --> 00:11:46.540
You're hoping we'll
either find another carrier

224
00:11:46.542 --> 00:11:48.373
or cut you an enormous check.

225
00:11:48.384 --> 00:11:49.584
Win-win for you!

226
00:11:49.595 --> 00:11:51.778
I assure you. neither
is going to happen.

227
00:11:51.780 --> 00:11:53.608
What will happen is very simple...

228
00:11:53.619 --> 00:11:55.170
you're going to do right by us

229
00:11:55.181 --> 00:11:56.916
or we will compel you to do so.

230
00:11:56.927 --> 00:11:59.519
- What do you mean by "compel"?
- You know exactly what I mean.

231
00:11:59.521 --> 00:12:02.389
If you're threatening litigation.
I'm afraid this meeting is over.

232
00:12:02.400 --> 00:12:04.010
Then it's over.

233
00:12:04.689 --> 00:12:06.337
Thank you for your time.

234
00:12:06.357 --> 00:12:08.908
Mr. Hamlin. Mr. McGill.

235
00:12:19.041 --> 00:12:21.030
All right. Where do we begin?

236
00:12:21.041 --> 00:12:23.577
Francis should start
digging into regulations.

237
00:12:23.579 --> 00:12:26.213
I'm sorry I don't have the code sections

238
00:12:26.215 --> 00:12:27.647
at my fingertips just now.

239
00:12:27.649 --> 00:12:29.449
Let's pull a team of associates

240
00:12:29.451 --> 00:12:32.649
and get them looking at every
angle of injunctive relief.

241
00:12:32.660 --> 00:12:34.004
Before close of business...

242
00:12:34.015 --> 00:12:36.389
... we're going to hit Santa
Rosa with a demand letter

243
00:12:36.391 --> 00:12:38.158
that'll make their heads spin.

244
00:12:38.160 --> 00:12:40.227
Odds are. inside a week.

245
00:12:40.229 --> 00:12:42.090
they'll be sitting at the table again.

246
00:12:42.101 --> 00:12:43.996
And if not...

247
00:12:43.999 --> 00:12:46.765
well. we've never
shied away from a fight.

248
00:12:50.626 --> 00:12:52.584
Chuck. do you remember Al McConnell?

249
00:12:52.595 --> 00:12:54.474
Of course. Helluva litigator.

250
00:12:54.476 --> 00:12:55.939
Retired now. isn't he?

251
00:12:55.950 --> 00:12:58.248
He's a professor at UNM now.

252
00:12:58.259 --> 00:13:01.248
Wrote a fantastic book on
SCOTUS during Reconstruction.

253
00:13:01.250 --> 00:13:02.482
Fascinating stuff.

254
00:13:02.484 --> 00:13:03.634
Okay...

255
00:13:03.645 --> 00:13:06.342
I was talking to him. and he mentioned

256
00:13:06.353 --> 00:13:09.295
he'd love you to come
speak to his One-Ls.

257
00:13:09.306 --> 00:13:12.376
Maybe make it a regular
thing. if you wanted.

258
00:13:13.849 --> 00:13:15.629
What are you talking about. Howard?

259
00:13:15.631 --> 00:13:17.803
What I'm saying is...

260
00:13:17.814 --> 00:13:20.667
maybe it's time to hang up your spurs.

261
00:13:21.189 --> 00:13:23.060
Become partner emeritus...

262
00:13:23.071 --> 00:13:25.639
leave your name on the firm
but focus on your legacy.

263
00:13:25.641 --> 00:13:29.076
You always said you wanted to
work on the Commerce Clause...

264
00:13:29.087 --> 00:13:30.787
you can write the book on it.

265
00:13:30.798 --> 00:13:33.632
And no longer be a practicing lawyer.

266
00:13:35.399 --> 00:13:38.053
Chuck. there's more to life than this.

267
00:13:38.064 --> 00:13:40.887
That day is far in the future. Howard.

268
00:13:40.889 --> 00:13:43.689
And I don't appreciate the suggestion.

269
00:13:45.454 --> 00:13:47.360
What if it's not a suggestion?

270
00:13:47.362 --> 00:13:48.540
Meaning?

271
00:13:48.551 --> 00:13:51.464
Meaning. if enough people
tell you that you're drunk.

272
00:13:51.466 --> 00:13:53.733
maybe it's time to sit down.

273
00:13:56.370 --> 00:13:59.749
You want me to retire
over this... insurance?!

274
00:13:59.760 --> 00:14:01.190
It's not just the insurance.

275
00:14:01.201 --> 00:14:04.035
That's the straw that
broke the camel's back.

276
00:14:05.393 --> 00:14:08.081
So this is about my condition.

277
00:14:08.363 --> 00:14:09.745
Look!

278
00:14:10.418 --> 00:14:11.745
Look!

279
00:14:14.138 --> 00:14:15.783
You see?

280
00:14:16.784 --> 00:14:18.692
See?

281
00:14:18.694 --> 00:14:20.260
I'm better!

282
00:14:20.698 --> 00:14:23.065
Howard. I'm fine!

283
00:14:26.823 --> 00:14:29.328
This is not what "fine" looks like.

284
00:14:33.211 --> 00:14:35.742
Chuck. you are the best
legal mind I've ever known.

285
00:14:35.744 --> 00:14:37.344
Hands down.

286
00:14:37.964 --> 00:14:40.426
But your decision-making has become...

287
00:14:40.437 --> 00:14:42.057
unpredictable.

288
00:14:43.161 --> 00:14:46.666
And I can't be partners with
someone whose judgment I don't trust.

289
00:14:51.256 --> 00:14:52.675
Chuck...

290
00:15:04.050 --> 00:15:07.828
This right here is the
Texas-New Mexico border.

291
00:15:08.980 --> 00:15:13.016
Now. all of my wells are square...

292
00:15:13.026 --> 00:15:15.022
on the Texas side.

293
00:15:15.033 --> 00:15:18.241
When I negotiated for the
mineral and property rights.

294
00:15:18.253 --> 00:15:22.461
the surveyors said that the
next nearest pool extended to...

295
00:15:26.509 --> 00:15:28.127
about here.

296
00:15:28.138 --> 00:15:29.584
Right.

297
00:15:29.595 --> 00:15:31.806
But... after some extraction.

298
00:15:31.817 --> 00:15:34.666
the west wall of the salt dome gave way.

299
00:15:34.677 --> 00:15:37.084
opening up another pool
that extends... what...

300
00:15:37.095 --> 00:15:38.743
100 yards over the border?

301
00:15:38.745 --> 00:15:40.267
That's about the size of it. yeah.

302
00:15:40.285 --> 00:15:43.053
And now you have New Mexico
rights holders to deal with.

303
00:15:43.556 --> 00:15:45.462
You know. they should get
profit on what's theirs.

304
00:15:45.473 --> 00:15:47.462
but now I've got two
states coming after me

305
00:15:47.473 --> 00:15:49.673
for taxes on each and every gallon.

306
00:15:51.047 --> 00:15:53.025
No equipment crosses the border?

307
00:15:53.036 --> 00:15:54.635
No. ma'am.

308
00:15:54.653 --> 00:15:57.111
Nothing below the surface. like the...

309
00:15:58.197 --> 00:15:59.954
What... is it a drill bit?

310
00:15:59.956 --> 00:16:02.697
It would be the sucker rod at
this point. but no. none of that.

311
00:16:02.708 --> 00:16:04.492
Only on the Texas side.

312
00:16:04.494 --> 00:16:07.995
But that's not stopping New
Mexico from trying to bleed me.

313
00:16:08.355 --> 00:16:10.596
You said on the phone
you have a solution.

314
00:16:11.901 --> 00:16:14.299
You don't negotiate a lease
with the rights holders.

315
00:16:14.310 --> 00:16:16.879
- You offer to pay them damages.
- Damages?

316
00:16:16.890 --> 00:16:19.020
For diminishing their resource.

317
00:16:19.035 --> 00:16:22.630
A significant fraction of the
value of the New Mexico portion.

318
00:16:22.641 --> 00:16:24.848
but without paying for
the rights themselves.

319
00:16:25.248 --> 00:16:27.239
So a kind of a payoff.

320
00:16:28.449 --> 00:16:30.395
Then you don't get hit with the taxes.

321
00:16:30.406 --> 00:16:32.539
You think you can make that fly?

322
00:16:32.550 --> 00:16:35.051
If someone came to me with this offer...

323
00:16:35.062 --> 00:16:36.924
I'd sure as hell take it.

324
00:16:36.926 --> 00:16:39.393
Wish I'd called you sooner.

325
00:16:39.965 --> 00:16:41.700
Way they're makin' noise.

326
00:16:41.711 --> 00:16:44.348
if I don't get this thing wrapped
up by the end of the quarter.

327
00:16:44.359 --> 00:16:47.641
I'm pretty sure the tax
boys are gonna take me apart.

328
00:16:47.652 --> 00:16:50.153
And that's two weeks from now?

329
00:16:52.582 --> 00:16:54.108
I can do it by then.

330
00:16:54.110 --> 00:16:55.676
Really?

331
00:16:55.678 --> 00:16:57.566
If we can get all the
rights holders in one place.

332
00:16:57.577 --> 00:17:00.111
I can walk them through
what we're proposing.

333
00:17:00.122 --> 00:17:02.283
If they're smart. they'll go for it.

334
00:17:02.285 --> 00:17:03.784
Well. hot damn.

335
00:17:06.430 --> 00:17:09.313
Kevin said you were a miracle
worker. but I didn't believe him.

336
00:17:09.324 --> 00:17:11.125
I'm startin' to.

337
00:17:11.127 --> 00:17:14.528
Yeah. well. let me work that
miracle first. then we'll talk.

338
00:17:14.530 --> 00:17:15.963
You know the way outta here?

339
00:17:15.965 --> 00:17:19.344
I got a drillhead that's acting up on me

340
00:17:19.355 --> 00:17:21.902
out on the north forty I gotta check.

341
00:17:21.904 --> 00:17:23.370
Yeah. I'm good.

342
00:17:23.372 --> 00:17:24.735
You need anything from me.

343
00:17:24.746 --> 00:17:26.438
you got my cell. Call me.

344
00:17:26.449 --> 00:17:27.899
Will do.

345
00:17:48.465 --> 00:17:51.597
Billy Gatwood meeting
notes. Contact Gatwood Oil.

346
00:17:51.608 --> 00:17:54.949
Get names and numbers for
New Mexico rights holders...

347
00:17:59.561 --> 00:18:01.058
Shit!

348
00:19:00.836 --> 00:19:02.703
No. no. no. no!

349
00:19:02.705 --> 00:19:04.838
No. no. no! Shit!

350
00:19:29.643 --> 00:19:32.695
Continuing notes from
Gatwood Oil meeting.

351
00:19:32.706 --> 00:19:34.948
Contact rights holders.

352
00:19:34.959 --> 00:19:36.948
begin scheduling.

353
00:20:00.696 --> 00:20:02.129
Howard!

354
00:20:04.498 --> 00:20:08.535
- What are you doing here. Jimmy?
- We have business to discuss.

355
00:20:08.537 --> 00:20:10.437
Is this about Chuck?

356
00:20:10.439 --> 00:20:12.239
Who?

357
00:20:12.241 --> 00:20:14.918
If you actually have business.
then call my secretary.

358
00:20:14.929 --> 00:20:17.644
I did. She stonewalled
me. as if you didn't know.

359
00:20:17.646 --> 00:20:19.102
Sandpiper.

360
00:20:19.113 --> 00:20:21.215
- What about it?
- It's time to settle.

361
00:20:21.217 --> 00:20:22.831
I-I saw the current offer.

362
00:20:22.842 --> 00:20:25.737
The clients make their losses
back. plus a solid chunk of change.

363
00:20:26.912 --> 00:20:28.752
Not that it's any of your business.

364
00:20:28.763 --> 00:20:31.552
but we project a final number
far higher than the current offer.

365
00:20:31.563 --> 00:20:33.365
I get it. I get it. You hold out.

366
00:20:33.376 --> 00:20:35.763
maybe you squeeze a grand
more for each client.

367
00:20:35.774 --> 00:20:38.021
Meanwhile. HHM nets a few million.

368
00:20:38.045 --> 00:20:40.893
You know. you're screwing the
clients for your own benefit.

369
00:20:40.904 --> 00:20:43.904
Oh. so now you're
worried about the clients?

370
00:20:43.906 --> 00:20:45.521
It's the right thing
to do. and you know it.

371
00:20:45.532 --> 00:20:47.041
Please.

372
00:20:47.052 --> 00:20:49.910
All you care about is
your share of the payout.

373
00:20:51.103 --> 00:20:53.177
It's like talking to Gollum.

374
00:20:53.188 --> 00:20:56.081
You're transparent. And pathetic.

375
00:20:57.520 --> 00:20:59.427
You want a handout?

376
00:21:00.888 --> 00:21:02.013
Here.

377
00:21:04.093 --> 00:21:05.318
Huh?

378
00:21:06.495 --> 00:21:08.299
Next time...

379
00:21:08.310 --> 00:21:10.130
why don't you bring a tin cup?

380
00:21:10.132 --> 00:21:12.045
It'd be more honest.

381
00:21:13.536 --> 00:21:16.136
Listen. Howard. settle
this and settle it now.

382
00:21:16.138 --> 00:21:17.904
It's in everyone's best interests!

383
00:21:17.915 --> 00:21:19.973
Meaning it's in your best interests.

384
00:21:19.975 --> 00:21:21.942
And if we don't. what are you gonna do?

385
00:21:21.944 --> 00:21:23.677
Peel off some members of the class.

386
00:21:23.679 --> 00:21:25.581
leak some insider info to Schweikart?

387
00:21:25.592 --> 00:21:27.781
Oh. I doubt it. I know you're low enough

388
00:21:27.783 --> 00:21:29.650
to do something like that.
but you're too damn greedy.

389
00:21:29.652 --> 00:21:30.892
You do any of that.

390
00:21:30.903 --> 00:21:33.197
and you'll be jeopardizing your payday.

391
00:21:34.190 --> 00:21:36.339
You'll get your damn money.

392
00:21:36.350 --> 00:21:38.142
You're just gonna have to wait for it.

393
