00:24:10.056 --> 00:24:11.938
_

410
00:24:12.025 --> 00:24:13.830
_

411
00:25:05.150 --> 00:25:06.767
Well. we go around about.

412
00:25:06.791 --> 00:25:09.330
you know. six times. I think.

413
00:25:09.360 --> 00:25:13.838
I think we're... Yeah.
I think... I think so.

414
00:25:14.861 --> 00:25:16.322
I know!

415
00:25:16.333 --> 00:25:18.133
This is so good for you.

416
00:25:18.135 --> 00:25:19.377
Hello. ladies.

417
00:25:19.388 --> 00:25:20.836
Good morning.

418
00:25:20.838 --> 00:25:22.271
- Hi! Jimmy!
- Hi. Jimmy.

419
00:25:22.273 --> 00:25:23.639
Jimmy!

420
00:25:23.641 --> 00:25:26.208
Oh. y-you... you girls
go on a little bit.

421
00:25:26.210 --> 00:25:28.119
I'll... I'll catch up with you.

422
00:25:28.130 --> 00:25:29.362
Jimmy!

423
00:25:29.373 --> 00:25:30.658
Wow. Irene!

424
00:25:30.669 --> 00:25:32.948
Fancy running into
you twice in one week.

425
00:25:32.950 --> 00:25:34.383
How lucky am I?

426
00:25:34.385 --> 00:25:35.736
Y-You're a mall-walker?

427
00:25:35.747 --> 00:25:37.747
- I had no idea!
- Me?

428
00:25:37.758 --> 00:25:39.521
Oh. yeah. Big time.

429
00:25:39.523 --> 00:25:41.790
I mean. it's great for cardio.

430
00:25:41.792 --> 00:25:45.585
Hamstrings. glutes. I-T band.

431
00:25:45.596 --> 00:25:47.163
I'm a huge mall-walker.

432
00:25:47.174 --> 00:25:49.007
Been out of the game for awhile.

433
00:25:49.018 --> 00:25:50.866
Developed this damn plantar fasciitis.

434
00:25:50.868 --> 00:25:52.534
- Mnh. Mnh.
- Hurts like a bear.

435
00:25:52.536 --> 00:25:54.939
Oh. I'm so sorry to hear about that.

436
00:25:54.950 --> 00:25:56.817
Well. hey.

437
00:25:56.828 --> 00:25:58.807
I got the cure right here.

438
00:25:59.861 --> 00:26:01.176
Pow!

439
00:26:01.178 --> 00:26:04.847
These have a special
gel and resistance coils

440
00:26:04.849 --> 00:26:06.081
and buncha stuff.

441
00:26:06.083 --> 00:26:08.135
It's like walkin' on pillows.

442
00:26:08.146 --> 00:26:11.186
Well. they... they...
they look comfortable.

443
00:26:11.188 --> 00:26:12.588
You like 'em?

444
00:26:12.590 --> 00:26:15.858
Well. they... they're quite stylish.

445
00:26:15.860 --> 00:26:18.181
Hey. y'know what?

446
00:26:18.192 --> 00:26:20.481
I bought a pair for my
girlfriend. and they don't fit her.

447
00:26:20.492 --> 00:26:22.598
And the store has this...
wouldn't you know it?...

448
00:26:22.600 --> 00:26:24.766
- no-refunds policy.
- Oh.

449
00:26:24.768 --> 00:26:26.230
What size are you?

450
00:26:27.175 --> 00:26:29.996
7 1/2. 7 1/2.

451
00:26:31.652 --> 00:26:33.996
Oh. there we go.

452
00:26:41.585 --> 00:26:42.951
How does that feel?

453
00:26:42.953 --> 00:26:44.253
Oh!

454
00:26:45.499 --> 00:26:48.367
Oh. I-I see what you mean. They...

455
00:26:48.378 --> 00:26:52.688
They are so nice. and
they fit like a dream!

456
00:26:52.699 --> 00:26:55.531
But I-I can't take
these for free. Jimmy.

457
00:26:55.533 --> 00:26:57.196
Oh. please.

458
00:26:57.207 --> 00:26:59.744
There is one thing you could do for me?

459
00:26:59.755 --> 00:27:01.255
What's that?

460
00:27:01.574 --> 00:27:03.230
Don't tell the other
folks I gave 'em to ya.

461
00:27:03.241 --> 00:27:05.730
I don't want to look like
I'm playing favorites.

462
00:27:06.243 --> 00:27:08.903
- My lips are sealed.
- Then you go and enjoy those.

463
00:27:08.914 --> 00:27:10.208
I'm gonna go get my heart rate back up.

464
00:27:10.219 --> 00:27:11.958
- Oh. thank you!
- And I'll see you later.

465
00:27:11.976 --> 00:27:14.233
Thank you so much. Jimmy!

466
00:27:23.290 --> 00:27:25.388
... Right hand. friends...
the hand of love.

467
00:27:25.755 --> 00:27:27.429
Now. watch. and I'll show
you the story of life.

468
00:27:27.431 --> 00:27:29.557
You got some questions.
It's only natural.

469
00:27:29.568 --> 00:27:32.734
And the truth is. if Irene settles...

470
00:27:32.736 --> 00:27:34.736
you'd get some money.

471
00:27:36.083 --> 00:27:39.466
But. I mean. it's not like
you guys need it. right?

472
00:27:39.977 --> 00:27:42.708
On the other hand. I did
get a look at their offer.

473
00:27:42.719 --> 00:27:45.463
I don't want to speak
out of school. but...

474
00:27:45.474 --> 00:27:47.416
it's. uh...

475
00:27:48.161 --> 00:27:52.247
But I mean. hey. everyone's
situation is different.

476
00:27:52.661 --> 00:27:55.169
Maybe Irene just doesn't need the money.

477
00:27:55.193 --> 00:27:57.092
I mean. I don't know for a fact. but...

478
00:27:57.094 --> 00:28:00.122
when you see someone
buying nice new things...

479
00:28:00.133 --> 00:28:02.297
- Like those shoes.
- ... like those shoes.

480
00:28:02.299 --> 00:28:03.779
Uh-huh.

481
00:28:04.301 --> 00:28:06.602
Ah. I mean. those must
have cost a pretty penny.

482
00:28:06.604 --> 00:28:08.278
I mean. if she can afford those.

483
00:28:08.289 --> 00:28:09.938
she's walkin' on easy street.

484
00:28:09.940 --> 00:28:12.356
And there's something else...

485
00:28:12.606 --> 00:28:14.387
y'know. The lawyers.

486
00:28:14.398 --> 00:28:16.114
I mean...

487
00:28:16.176 --> 00:28:18.832
that's the lawyer's
share of the settlement.

488
00:28:18.843 --> 00:28:22.535
And your share is...
boop!... this much. Doo!

489
00:28:22.546 --> 00:28:27.589
If Irene holds out. the
lawyers get this much more...

490
00:28:27.591 --> 00:28:31.246
and you are gonna get this much more.

491
00:28:31.257 --> 00:28:33.540
Doesn't seem like much difference.

492
00:28:33.582 --> 00:28:36.202
I know. but that's how it works.

493
00:28:36.213 --> 00:28:37.946
And Irene knows it. too.

494
00:28:37.957 --> 00:28:40.165
I mean. the lawyers
have explained it to her.

495
00:28:40.176 --> 00:28:42.856
It's crazy. but it's all up to Irene.

496
00:28:42.887 --> 00:28:45.607
After all. she is the
Class Representative.

497
00:28:45.609 --> 00:28:48.210
Does that mean that she gets more?

498
00:28:48.212 --> 00:28:49.778
No. No.

499
00:28:49.780 --> 00:28:52.989
Just means in the eyes of
the court. she's special.

500
00:28:53.000 --> 00:28:56.451
She's like your
congressman or ambassador.

501
00:28:56.453 --> 00:28:58.320
Is there anything we can do?

502
00:28:58.322 --> 00:29:02.235
No. No. You can't do anything.

503
00:29:02.246 --> 00:29:03.659
I can't do anything.

504
00:29:05.086 --> 00:29:06.695
Only Irene.

505
00:29:08.399 --> 00:29:11.199
She probably knows what's best.

506
00:29:11.201 --> 00:29:14.369
I'm sure she's taking
your feelings into account.

507
00:29:14.371 --> 00:29:16.138
Hey. look at the big picture.

508
00:29:16.140 --> 00:29:19.164
Who needs money when you
got the moral high ground?

509
00:29:25.554 --> 00:29:27.200
Yoo-hoo!

510
00:29:27.211 --> 00:29:28.726
Rose!

511
00:29:29.486 --> 00:29:30.968
Helen!

512
00:29:31.914 --> 00:29:33.880
Ladies?!

513
00:29:33.891 --> 00:29:35.828
Ladies!

514
00:30:18.208 --> 00:30:19.814
Ignacio?

