Julie. what's up? From Chuck.

551
00:33:28.992 --> 00:33:30.992
It came via messenger...
the instructions say

552
00:33:30.994 --> 00:33:33.544
he wants you to read
it as soon as possible.

553
00:33:35.466 --> 00:33:36.708
Mm-hmm.

554
00:33:37.255 --> 00:33:39.000
Uh. here's what I need you to do.

555
00:33:39.002 --> 00:33:42.737
Call around. Find someplace
special for the retirement party.

556
00:33:42.739 --> 00:33:44.606
Something classy. old-school.

557
00:33:44.608 --> 00:33:46.308
Uh. La Posada. maybe.

558
00:33:46.310 --> 00:33:49.619
And a band. Something jazzy. Upbeat.

559
00:33:49.630 --> 00:33:50.786
Find what's available.

560
00:33:50.797 --> 00:33:52.184
- Let's set it up.
- Okay.

561
00:34:06.165 --> 00:34:08.001
Goddamit. Chuck.

562
00:34:10.454 --> 00:34:12.579
You're suing Hamlin. Hamlin. McGill?

563
00:34:12.590 --> 00:34:14.297
Come on in. Howard.

564
00:34:18.034 --> 00:34:19.680
You turned the lights on.

565
00:34:19.691 --> 00:34:23.211
I told you... I'm back to normal.

566
00:34:23.213 --> 00:34:26.693
And yes. I am suing HHM
for breach of contract.

567
00:34:26.704 --> 00:34:28.712
Do you have any idea what you're doing?

568
00:34:28.723 --> 00:34:30.485
I believe I do.

569
00:34:30.496 --> 00:34:32.454
I'm calling your bluff.

570
00:34:32.456 --> 00:34:35.224
This is my firm. I built it.

571
00:34:35.235 --> 00:34:38.693
Your father was working in a
two-room office when I joined him.

572
00:34:38.695 --> 00:34:41.701
And you I tutored for the bar exam.

573
00:34:41.712 --> 00:34:43.131
You're not kicking me out.

574
00:34:43.133 --> 00:34:45.467
If you can't "trust my
judgment." as you say.

575
00:34:45.469 --> 00:34:46.801
so be it.

576
00:34:46.803 --> 00:34:49.747
but you're gonna have
to pay me for my share.

577
00:34:49.758 --> 00:34:52.807
I believe it comes to around $8 million.

578
00:34:52.809 --> 00:34:55.430
We both know the firm
doesn't have the money.

579
00:34:56.782 --> 00:34:59.716
You'd rather tear down HHM than retire?

580
00:34:59.727 --> 00:35:02.642
You think I'm trouble
now? As your partner?

581
00:35:02.653 --> 00:35:04.743
Imagine me as your enemy.

582
00:35:09.175 --> 00:35:10.508
Chuck...

583
00:35:11.370 --> 00:35:12.894
the damage that you're going to do...

584
00:35:12.896 --> 00:35:14.886
If you'd like to discuss this further.

585
00:35:14.897 --> 00:35:17.109
we can... in court.

586
00:35:17.120 --> 00:35:18.700
Until then...

587
00:35:19.550 --> 00:35:22.070
what else is there to say?

588
00:35:40.527 --> 00:35:42.557
Blue pot. Red wine.

589
00:35:42.559 --> 00:35:44.359
Black burner.

590
00:35:44.361 --> 00:35:46.394
Blue pot. Red wine.

591
00:35:47.011 --> 00:35:50.128
Black burner. Blue pot.
Red wine. Black burner.

592
00:36:38.617 --> 00:36:40.317
I got hot hands.

593
00:36:40.319 --> 00:36:43.062
I got hot hands! I know
this is gonna be the one!

594
00:36:43.073 --> 00:36:45.456
B-9!

595
00:36:45.504 --> 00:36:49.930
Let's hope that biopsy comes back "B-9."

596
00:36:49.941 --> 00:36:51.523
B-9.

597
00:36:54.914 --> 00:36:57.094
Okay... what's next?

598
00:36:58.449 --> 00:37:00.648
We got... I-29.

599
00:37:00.659 --> 00:37:03.039
I remember when I was 29.

600
00:37:03.050 --> 00:37:05.284
Bet you do. too.

601
00:37:05.295 --> 00:37:07.626
I-29.

602
00:37:13.312 --> 00:37:16.906
Here comes O-62.

603
00:37:17.883 --> 00:37:19.590
Oh. my God.

604
00:37:19.592 --> 00:37:21.937
Have I called 62 of these already?

605
00:37:21.948 --> 00:37:25.062
It feels like it. O-62.

606
00:37:26.039 --> 00:37:28.273
Here we have B-2.

607
00:37:28.284 --> 00:37:29.719
B-2.

608
00:37:29.730 --> 00:37:32.436
Well. tonight is all bingo.

609
00:37:32.438 --> 00:37:33.781
Here it comes.

610
00:37:33.792 --> 00:37:36.440
O-70. Anyone? O-70.

611
00:37:37.062 --> 00:37:39.164
All right. No takers.

612
00:37:39.175 --> 00:37:40.719
Boom!

613
00:37:41.281 --> 00:37:42.880
G-55.

614
00:37:42.882 --> 00:37:44.282
G-55.

615
00:37:44.284 --> 00:37:45.950
Oh. my God! Bingo!

616
00:37:45.952 --> 00:37:47.289
I got bingo!

617
00:37:47.300 --> 00:37:49.520
Big Paul. bring it up.

618
00:37:49.522 --> 00:37:51.192
Kelly. take a look.

619
00:37:51.203 --> 00:37:53.672
We may have a winner.

620
00:37:54.254 --> 00:37:57.109
Kelly. tell me... have we got it?

621
00:37:57.120 --> 00:37:58.416
We have a bingo!

622
00:37:58.427 --> 00:38:00.894
Paul. step up to the winner's circle.

623
00:38:00.905 --> 00:38:02.273
Let's hear it for him!

624
00:38:02.284 --> 00:38:04.517
Let's give him a big round of applause!

625
00:38:06.806 --> 00:38:09.140
Okay. New game. new cards.

626
00:38:09.142 --> 00:38:10.641
Here they come.

627
00:38:10.643 --> 00:38:13.023
Get yourself some new cards. New cards.

628
00:38:14.681 --> 00:38:17.271
The helpers have them.
You can have one. two.

629
00:38:17.282 --> 00:38:19.586
You can have up to four. as you know.

630
00:38:19.984 --> 00:38:22.778
Here's a lucky blue one for you.

631
00:38:22.789 --> 00:38:26.289
All right. Take your cards
so we can start a new game.

632
00:38:26.291 --> 00:38:29.258
There you go. Add that to your stack.

633
00:38:30.391 --> 00:38:31.928
All right. Get your cards.

634
00:38:31.930 --> 00:38:34.481
Hey. Irene. you feeling lucky today?

635
00:38:34.492 --> 00:38:36.099
I-I guess so.

636
00:38:36.101 --> 00:38:38.835
All right. Well. here's one on me...

637
00:38:38.837 --> 00:38:40.303
just for you.

638
00:38:41.109 --> 00:38:46.203
All right. I sold my
soul for B-I-N-G-and-O!

639
00:38:46.711 --> 00:38:49.242
Let's clear the table.

640
00:39:08.768 --> 00:39:10.253
Load it up.

641
00:39:16.745 --> 00:39:18.474
Locked and loaded.

642
00:39:25.549 --> 00:39:27.568
Here comes a new game.

643
00:39:32.323 --> 00:39:34.824
First number up...

644
00:39:36.815 --> 00:39:39.420
it's N-31.

645
00:39:39.431 --> 00:39:40.971
"N" for "Nancy."

646
00:39:40.982 --> 00:39:44.195
31 for the number of times
she told me to take a hike.

647
00:39:44.206 --> 00:39:47.143
N-31.

648
00:39:49.378 --> 00:39:51.156
G-48.

649
00:39:51.167 --> 00:39:53.620
"G" for the Greatest Generation.

650
00:39:53.631 --> 00:39:56.746
48 for "Dewey Defeats Truman."

651
00:39:56.748 --> 00:40:00.281
Here's I-25... the big "I."

652
00:40:00.292 --> 00:40:01.835
I-25.

653
00:40:01.885 --> 00:40:05.755
It's B-12. like the vitamin.

654
00:40:13.808 --> 00:40:15.398
O-67!

655
00:40:15.400 --> 00:40:18.543
Anybody? I got a good
feeling about this.

656
00:40:18.554 --> 00:40:21.144
O-67!

657
00:40:22.988 --> 00:40:26.368
I-I-I think... Bingo!

658
00:40:26.379 --> 00:40:27.643
Who is that?

659
00:40:27.645 --> 00:40:29.215
Come on up.

660
00:40:29.972 --> 00:40:34.172
Irene! Irene. come on up here. dear.

661
00:40:34.183 --> 00:40:36.891
Bring it up to Kelly. Let's take a look.

662
00:40:36.902 --> 00:40:39.155
Kelly has to check your card.

663
00:40:40.991 --> 00:40:43.091
Here she comes.

664
00:40:47.644 --> 00:40:49.488
Could be...

665
00:40:52.136 --> 00:40:54.437
Oh. my goodness.

666
00:40:54.439 --> 00:40:58.407
It is a bingo for Irene!

667
00:40:58.409 --> 00:41:00.610
Let's hear it for Irene Landry!

668
00:41:02.488 --> 00:41:05.676
Give it up for the big
winner. Irene Landry!

669
00:41:07.318 --> 00:41:09.598
Fastest bingo of the night!

670
00:41:09.609 --> 00:41:12.088
Come on. Let's hear it for Irene.

671
00:41:12.090 --> 00:41:13.374
Oh!

672
00:41:15.026 --> 00:41:16.226
Irene...

673
00:41:16.237 --> 00:41:17.285
where ya goin'?

674
00:41:17.296 --> 00:41:19.492
Hey. you know what? Take over.

675
00:41:21.038 --> 00:41:23.266
Okay. Time for a new game.

676
00:41:23.268 --> 00:41:26.152
Uh. let's get some
cards out for everyone.

677
00:41:31.687 --> 00:41:33.025
Hey.

678
00:41:33.036 --> 00:41:35.108
What's going on? You okay?

679
00:41:37.054 --> 00:41:39.121
Aww. Don't do that.

680
00:41:39.132 --> 00:41:42.054
Your mascara's gonna run all over.

681
00:41:44.296 --> 00:41:46.489
Irene. come on.

682
00:41:46.491 --> 00:41:48.249
What's wrong?

683
00:41:50.128 --> 00:41:52.749
They've all turned on me.

684
00:41:54.081 --> 00:41:55.681
Who has?

685
00:41:56.134 --> 00:41:57.832
My friends!

686
00:41:57.869 --> 00:42:01.043
Helen. Rose. Myrtle.

687
00:42:01.054 --> 00:42:03.371
All of them.

688
00:42:03.382 --> 00:42:05.832
What? No!

689
00:42:05.843 --> 00:42:07.851
Yes!

690
00:42:09.147 --> 00:42:11.499
They're so cold.

691
00:42:12.640 --> 00:42:16.434
When I walk past them.
they stop talking.

692
00:42:16.436 --> 00:42:18.312
I-I-I hear them whispering

693
00:42:18.323 --> 00:42:21.157
when... when they think I'm not there.

694
00:42:21.159 --> 00:42:23.757
It's just so...

695
00:42:23.928 --> 00:42:25.481
- It's so cruel.
- Mnh.

696
00:42:25.492 --> 00:42:27.663
And I don't even know why.

697
00:42:32.648 --> 00:42:34.937
I think. uh...

698
00:42:34.939 --> 00:42:37.039
maybe I do.

699
00:42:38.848 --> 00:42:40.713
You do?

700
00:42:44.191 --> 00:42:46.766
Could it be the settlement?

701
00:42:46.777 --> 00:42:49.461
I mean. maybe they...

702
00:42:49.472 --> 00:42:51.844
want the money.

703
00:42:51.855 --> 00:42:55.375
you know. to improve their lives?

704
00:42:55.386 --> 00:42:58.561
I had no idea any of them needed money.

705
00:42:58.563 --> 00:43:00.763
No one said anything to me.

706
00:43:00.765 --> 00:43:03.265
Well. maybe it's not
about the money itself.

707
00:43:03.267 --> 00:43:07.737
I mean... hello... who
wouldn't want more money?

708
00:43:07.739 --> 00:43:10.308
I mean. maybe it's the idea

709
00:43:10.319 --> 00:43:15.464
that they don't think you're
considering them. you know?

710
00:43:16.121 --> 00:43:18.247
Thinking of their needs?

711
00:43:18.249 --> 00:43:20.650
I-I-I didn't know.

712
00:43:20.652 --> 00:43:23.980
I don't want to hurt
them. They're my friends.

713
00:43:26.925 --> 00:43:29.392
I wish we never even
started this lawsuit.

714
00:43:29.394 --> 00:43:32.477
I just want everything
to go back the way it was.

715
00:43:35.488 --> 00:43:38.183
What should I do?

716
00:43:38.879 --> 00:43:41.418
What would you do?

717
00:43:43.574 --> 00:43:47.082
I mean. you know I'm
not a lawyer right now.

718
00:43:47.832 --> 00:43:49.612
Please?

719
00:43:51.073 --> 00:43:53.144
Should I settle?

720
00:43:57.480 --> 00:43:59.255
Irene...

721
00:44:02.673 --> 00:44:04.785
you listen to your heart.

722
00:44:16.939 --> 00:44:18.841
Uh. time?

723
00:44:18.843 --> 00:44:20.109
Two hours out.

724
00:44:20.111 --> 00:44:21.644
When did I say I was gonna leave?

725
00:44:21.646 --> 00:44:23.312
20 minutes ago.

726
00:44:24.049 --> 00:44:26.576
Uh. can I have some more coffee. please?

727
00:44:26.587 --> 00:44:28.400
Coming.

728
00:44:33.391 --> 00:44:36.383
Uh. I'm missing a survey
history in this one.

729
00:44:36.394 --> 00:44:38.922
On it. Sorry about that.

730
00:44:38.933 --> 00:44:40.469
Not a problem.

731
00:44:40.480 --> 00:44:42.164
Hey!

732
00:44:42.166 --> 00:44:44.667
Who's ready to have her life changed?

733
00:44:44.669 --> 00:44:46.202
Kim. did you hear me?

734
00:44:46.204 --> 00:44:48.270
Yep. Heard you. Life changed.

735
00:44:48.281 --> 00:44:52.074
Stop your work. both of you. for a sec.

736
00:44:52.076 --> 00:44:53.743
I-I got big. big news.

737
00:44:53.745 --> 00:44:55.578
Can you just tell us later. Jimmy?

738
00:44:55.580 --> 00:44:58.329
- I'm so late. it's not even funny.
- Mesa Verde can wait.

739
00:44:58.340 --> 00:45:01.183
- Look. I got Zafiro.
- It's not Mesa Verde.

740
00:45:01.185 --> 00:45:03.552
It's a new client. and if I mess
this up. it's a former client.

741
00:45:03.554 --> 00:45:05.654
I thought Mesa Verde
was your one and only.

742
00:45:05.656 --> 00:45:07.556
You know. it's go...
Ji... uh. I'm sorry.

743
00:45:07.567 --> 00:45:09.582
Jimmy. can I just explain
all this to you later? I'm...

744
00:45:09.593 --> 00:45:11.801
Sandpiper is settling.

745
00:45:12.430 --> 00:45:14.751
- What?
- Yeah.

746
00:45:14.762 --> 00:45:16.394
For a bundle.

747
00:45:17.293 --> 00:45:19.101
But th-they can't be settling.

748
00:45:19.103 --> 00:45:21.103
Class actions don't move that fast.

749
00:45:21.105 --> 00:45:23.339
Don't get bogged down in the details!

750
00:45:23.364 --> 00:45:26.082
Trust me... they're settling!

751
00:45:27.649 --> 00:45:28.915
Wow. that...

752
00:45:28.926 --> 00:45:30.694
- Yeah. Yeah!
- That's great. then.

753
00:45:30.705 --> 00:45:32.548
So. hey. let's celebrate.

754
00:45:32.550 --> 00:45:34.077
I can tell that you...

755
00:45:34.088 --> 00:45:36.385
pulled another
all-nighter here. you know?

756
00:45:36.387 --> 00:45:38.921
You... you got to stop
and smell the roses.

757
00:45:38.923 --> 00:45:41.924
Hey. who's got two
thumbs. a bottle of Zafiro.

758
00:45:41.926 --> 00:45:43.858
and 20% of the common fund?!

759
00:45:43.869 --> 00:45:45.060
- Huh?
- This guy!

760
00:45:45.062 --> 00:45:47.530
I know... you do. Uh. I
am happy for you. Jimmy.

761
00:45:47.532 --> 00:45:48.864
Be happy for us!

762
00:45:48.866 --> 00:45:51.178
This is the solution to everything.

763
00:45:51.189 --> 00:45:52.713
Okay. Francesca. could you
just put these all in my car?

764
00:45:52.724 --> 00:45:54.252
Kim.

765
00:45:54.263 --> 00:45:55.522
Yeah. Jimmy. I gotta go.

766
00:45:55.533 --> 00:45:57.428
Gimme five goddamn minutes.

767
00:45:57.439 --> 00:45:59.189
- I don't have five minutes.
- But you're already late.

768
00:45:59.200 --> 00:46:01.944
What's five more minutes?
So drive 60 instead of 55.

769
00:46:01.946 --> 00:46:03.557
- Jimmy!
- What?

770
00:46:03.568 --> 00:46:05.067
You're not hearing me.

771
00:46:05.078 --> 00:46:06.916
Our troubles are over! Come on!

772
00:46:06.918 --> 00:46:08.639
Jimmy. I'm leaving now.

773
00:46:08.650 --> 00:46:09.919
I'll be back in a few hours.

774
00:46:09.930 --> 00:46:11.119
Think of all the things
you want to say to me.

775
00:46:11.130 --> 00:46:12.746
and just say them to me later. okay?

776
00:46:12.757 --> 00:46:14.135
Bye.

777
00:46:25.682 --> 00:46:27.786
You. Shots.

778
00:46:27.820 --> 00:46:30.204
- Uh. I...
- Shots.

779
00:46:30.215 --> 00:46:32.081
We're celebrating.

780
00:46:38.055 --> 00:46:40.249
Cheers.

781
00:46:43.516 --> 00:46:44.797
Smooth.

782
00:46:47.992 --> 00:46:49.407
Yeah.

783
00:46:53.961 --> 00:46:57.933
Under the terms we're offering.
you get a substantial payment

784
00:46:57.935 --> 00:47:01.224
without any impact to your property
via drilling and extraction.

785
00:47:01.235 --> 00:47:02.605
And rather than waiting years to close.

786
00:47:02.607 --> 00:47:06.286
Mr. Gatwood is offering cash
on the barrel. right now.

787
00:47:06.297 --> 00:47:09.388
Given the cost of overhead. liabilities.

788
00:47:09.399 --> 00:47:11.680
and other burdens Mr. Gatwood assumes.

789
00:47:11.682 --> 00:47:14.243
we believe this offer is more than fair.

790
00:47:14.254 --> 00:47:15.850
We believe...

791
00:47:16.337 --> 00:47:19.852
we believe this offer is more than fair.

792
00:48:01.205 --> 00:48:02.890
Aah!

